This paper deals with the computational complexity of decision problems in autoepistemic logic, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves analyzing Boolean fragments of the logic, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses counting problems, which can be related to complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with propositional logic, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL).
